1. Game Description

Last Tower Defense is a 2D tower defense game where the player protects a base from waves of enemies.
Enemies spawn on one side of the map and follow a predefined path toward the base.
The player must place defensive towers on specific spots to destroy enemies before they reach the end.

The main goal is to survive all waves while keeping the base alive.
If too many enemies reach the base and its health drops to zero, the player loses.

The game runs in a desktop window. On the screen,
the player sees the map, enemy path, base, towers, enemies, gold amount, base HP, and current wave number.

2. Controls

The controls are simple and intuitive.

The player mainly uses the mouse to place towers. By clicking on an available build spot, a tower is placed if the player has enough gold.

Keyboard controls:

Space — start the next wave
Esc — pause the game
R — restart the game after win or lose

The focus is on mouse-based interaction for fast and удобное gameplay.

3. Player

In this game, the player does not control a character directly. The player acts as a strategist who defends the base.

The player has:

Base HP — health of the base.
If enemies reach the end, the base loses HP.

Gold — used to build towers.
Gold is earned by killing enemies.

Towers — the main defense system.
Towers automatically attack enemies within range.

The player must think strategically and place towers in the best positions to stop enemies.

4. Enemies

Enemies come in waves and move toward the base. Each enemy has health, speed, and reward value.

Types of enemies:

Basic Enemy — balanced stats
Average HP and speed.

Fast Enemy — quick but weak
Low HP, high speed.

Tank Enemy — slow but strong
High HP, low speed.

When enemies take damage, their HP decreases. When it reaches zero, they are destroyed and the player earns gold. If they reach the base, they deal damage.

5. Levels

The first version of the game will include one main level, but it should be well-designed.

The level includes:

a path for enemies
a base at the end
tower placement spots
map background
UI (HP, Gold, Wave)

The map should encourage strategic placement of towers. For example, corners and turns are better positions because towers can attack enemies longer.

In the future, more levels can be added with different layouts and difficulty.

6. Win / Lose Screen

There are two final states in the game.

Lose Screen appears when base HP reaches 0:

Game Over
Your base was destroyed
Press R to restart

Win Screen appears after all waves are completed:

Victory
You survived all waves
Press R to play again

This clearly shows the outcome and allows the player to restart quickly.

7. Art Style

The game uses a simple 2D visual style.

It can be pixel art or basic shapes if no assets are available.

The most important thing is clarity:

enemies are clearly visible
the path stands out from the background
towers are easy to recognize
the base is visually distinct
UI is clean and readable

Even with simple graphics, the game should look clean and organized.

8. Core Gameplay Loop

The gameplay loop is:

Player launches the game
Main menu appears
Player clicks Start
Level begins
Player places towers
Player presses Space to start a wave
Enemies move toward the base
Towers attack automatically
Player earns gold for kills
After all waves → win or lose